## Punishment for Crimes (33-40)

This section covers severe punishments:

**Waging war against God and His messenger** (33): those who fight against the Muslim community and spread terror face execution, crucifixion, amputation of opposite limbs, or exile. But the next verse immediately adds:

> *"Except for those who repent before you apprehend them. Know that God is Forgiving and Merciful."* (34)

If they repent before being caught, the punishment is dropped.

**Theft** (38): the punishment mentioned is cutting off the hand. Islamic jurisprudence has historically set a very high bar for this: the stolen item must exceed a minimum value, it must be taken from a secure place, the thief can't be stealing out of need, and multiple witnesses are required. In practice, the conditions are so strict that many scholars throughout history have rarely applied it.

